---
import SectionHeader from "./SectionHeader.astro";
---
<section id="readme" class="section section--readme">
  <SectionHeader idx={1} file="README.md" sub="// the bit recruiters actually read" />
  <div class="readme-card">
    <div class="readme-badges">
      <span class="badge"><b>build</b><i>passing</i></span>
      <span class="badge"><b>coverage</b><i>~74%</i></span>
      <span class="badge"><b>years-shipping</b><i>6+</i></span>
      <span class="badge"><b>last commit</b><i>today</i></span>
      <span class="badge"><b>license</b><i>be-kind</i></span>
    </div>
    <h3># about</h3>
    <p>
      Hi, I'm <b>Decembaek</b> (백12월). I design and engineer interface software — mostly the kind that
      sits between you and a database, and tries very hard not to embarrass either of you.
    </p>
    <p>
      I started as a designer who learned to code so my prototypes would stop lying to PMs, and slowly
      became the kind of engineer who refuses to ship a component without a spacing audit. I've worked
      on calendars, design systems, internal tooling, and one terrible cron job that I'd like to forget.
    </p>
    <h3># installation</h3>
    <pre class="code">$ git clone hi@decembaek.dev
$ cd decembaek && npm run coffee
✔ ready in 12.3s</pre>
    <h3># philosophy</h3>
    <ul class="philos">
      <li>small surface area, large craft.</li>
      <li>the worst tool is the one with a tutorial.</li>
      <li>if a button needs a tooltip, the button is wrong.</li>
      <li>write the README before the framework.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
